International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: Tue 7 Aug 2018
Source: WHDH TV 7NEWS, Associated Press (AP) report [edited]
https://whdh.com/news/peruvian-official-food-poisoning-kills-9-funeral-goers/


Authorities in Peru say at least 9 people have died from food poisoning following a funeral ceremony. Health officials said [on Tue 7 Aug 2018] that another 20 people were hospitalized with stomach pains and vomiting after a wake the previous day in the Ayacucho region of south-central Peru.

Regional health director Jhon Tinco tells a local radio station that the victims reported eating a meat dish and consuming a drink of fermented corn called chicha.

Tinco says health officials continue to investigate to determine what could have led to the deaths. He says the victims were taken to a local hospital where they died.

